news.title: High mortgage rates send homebuyers scrambling for relief
news.para: A recent snapshot by the Mortgage Bankers Association showed that ARMs accounted for 12.8% of all home loan applications in the week ended Oct. 14.

news.title: Government fixes Rs 7,409 crore indicative value for 'The Ashok' hotel
news.para: The Ashok and the adjacent hotel Samrat are among the eight India Tourism Development Corp assets listed under the National Monetisation Pipeline (NMP) announced by Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman last year.

news.title: China's bank sector issued $369 billion in real estate development loans in Jan-Oct 2022
news.para: Six of China's largest lenders have agreed to provide at least $130 in fresh credit to property developers, adding to recent regulatory support measures to ease a stifling cash crunch in the sector.

news.title: Relief for Rs 4.5 lakh allottees as Chandigarh approves need-based changes
news.para: The administration has allowed for free download of the standard drawings and no prior written consent requirement from all allottees in the block for making internal changes in a house, provision of additional door, constructing a lift and façade painting.

news.title: Keystone Realtors shares climb over 3% in debut trade
news.para: The stock listed at Rs 555, reflecting a gain of 2.58 per cent from the issue price on the BSE. It further rallied 5 per cent to Rs 568.25. Shares of the firm ended at Rs 557.80 apiece, higher by 3.10 per cent.

news.title: WSB Real Estate Debt Fund II invests Rs 165 crore in Sowparnika Homes
news.para: Vimal Jangla on behalf of WSBREDF II said, "This funding shall facilitate the delivery of ~2,750 homes in mid-income and affordable housing category."

news.title: Former local bodies officials appear in court in case related to CLU scam in Ludhiana
news.para: Both the officials appeared in the court for their statements in connection with the "missing" probe report in the CLU (change of land use) scam pertaining to Grand Manor homes - a residential project in Ludhiana's Ishar Nagar area.

news.title: CIDCO conducts lottery draw for 4,158 houses in Navi Mumbai
news.para: Under the scheme, 404 apartments were made available for EWS under PMAY housing scheme and the remaining 3,754 for general category, it said.

news.title: NOCs must to regularize construction under new impact few rule in Gujarat
news.para: ​The state urban development department has clarified that applications without no-objection certificates from Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA), Ahmedabad Fire and Emergency Services (AFES) and health department will be rejected.

news.title: Survey aimed at ending all land disputes: Andhra Pradesh CM
news.para: The CM said the government has taken up land survey with advanced technology in more than 17,000 revenue villages across the state.

news.title: Kochi corporation to extend deadline of Rajiv Awas Yojana project for fifth time
news.para: As per original schedule, the work should have been completed by 2018. Now, authorities are seeking the approval of the council to extend the deadline for the fifth time.

news.title: Telangana CM to meet district collectors to address Dharani woes
news.para: With complaints flooding from the public, farmers, political parties and even ruling party MLAs expressing fears of Dharani shadow on poll prospects, chief minister K Chandrasekhar Rao has now decided to address the concerns.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad: PCMC tells ward officers not to snap supply of property tax defaulters
news.para: The Pimpri Chinchwad civic body restored the connection within a few hours and now has issued a letter to its ward officers to refrain from snapping any more water connection.

news.title: Rajasthan housing board to sell flats at huge rebate to fund new luxury project
news.para: However, the board has also decided to sell 2,235 unsold flats in various projects constructed by it in the last 10 years at 25-50% discount to accommodate this project.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body's board okays transit-oriented development along RRTS corridor
news.para: The board decided to declare up to 1.5km on both sides of the rapid rail alignment as TOD zones, a move that would boost the real estate sector, and incorporate the same into the city’s Master Plan-2031.
